    "title": "Siku ya Bwana",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "siku ya bwana",
    "language": "swh",
    "content": "<p>Kifungu <em>Siku ya</em> <em>Bwana</em> kinaelezea wakati ambapo Mungu anawaadhibu maadui zake kwa adhabu ya haki. Wasio na Mungu wanapokea adhabu wanayostahili, wakati wenye haki wanapata wokovu wao kamili (tazama <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:16-Isa4:6\">Isaya 3:16–4:6</a>). Katika siku hii, Mungu anaonyesha udhibiti wake wenye nguvu juu ya uumbaji. Wakati Mungu anaonekana kwa utukufu, watu wanahisi hofu (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:10\">2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:19\">19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:21\">21</a>). Hii ni kwa sababu anachunguza mifumo yote ya msaada wa kibinadamu, ikijumuisha miundo ya kidini, kiuchumi, kijeshi, na kijamii.</p><p>Maneno haya yanapatikana kwanza katika unabii wa Amosi (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18\">Amosi 5:18</a>). Hata hivyo, hayakutokana na yeye pekee. Amosi alisahihisha kutoelewa kwa kawaida miongoni mwa Waisraeli. Walidhani Siku ya Bwana ingekuwa siku ya furaha na wokovu. Waliamini Mungu angehukumu maadui wa Israeli na kurejesha utawala wa Waisraeli juu ya Kanaani kubwa.</p><p>Hata hivyo, Amosi alionya kwamba Siku ya Bwana ingeleta giza, si mwanga. Hii ilikuwa kwa sababu watu walikuwa wakiasi dhidi ya Mungu (tazama <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:10-Amos5:12\">Amosi 5:10–12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:21-Amos5:27\">21–27</a>). Waisraeli walikuwa na uhakika kwamba Mungu alikuwa kila wakati upande wao. Lakini dhambi zao ziliwafanya kuwa maadui wa Mungu, wakistahili adhabu kamili.</p><p>Manabii mara nyingi walitumia msemo &quot;siku hiyo&quot; kuelezea tukio muhimu (tazama <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:11\">Isaya 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:1\">27:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:8\">Sefania 1:8</a>). Kwa sababu ya maonyo ya Mungu na dhambi za watu, manabii waliona &quot;siku hiyo&quot; kuwa karibu (tazama <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:15\">Yoeli 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:1\">2:1</a>). Walitumaini maonyo yao yangefanya watu wa Mungu watubu (tazama <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:1-Zeph2:3\">Sefania 2:1–3</a>). Kwa bahati mbaya, watu wengi walipuuza maonyo haya.</p><p>Siku ya Bwana ilifika kwa ufalme wa kaskazini wakati Ashuru ilipoharibu Samaria. Ilifika kwa ufalme wa kusini wakati Babeli ilipovamia na kuharibu Yerusalemu kati ya 605 na 586 Kabla ya Kristo (KK).</p><p>Siku ya Bwana ni ya maafa kwa wale wasiomcha Mungu. Nabii Yoeli analinganisha uharibifu wake na janga la nzige (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:1-Joel2:11\">Yoeli 1:1–2:11</a>). Hata hivyo, siku hii inawahakikishia watu wa Mungu kwamba yeye ni mkuu na mwenye haki. Ni siku ya wokovu kwa wale wanaotii manabii na &quot;kila mtu atakayeliitia jina la BWANA&quot; (tazama <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:31-Joel2:32\">Yoeli 2:31–32</a>).</p><p>Mungu yule yule anayewaletea maangamizi maadui zake atakuwa kimbilio na ngome kwa watu wake (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:16\">Yoeli 3:16</a>). Mataifa yanayotumiwa na Mungu kuhukumu Israeli na Yuda baadaye yatakutana na &quot;Siku ya Bwana&quot; yao wenyewe (tazama, kwa mfano, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:4-Isa13:22\">Isaya 13:4–22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:1-Ezek30:5\">Ezekieli 30:1–5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:15-Obad1:16\">Obadia 1:15–16</a>).</p><p>Manabii wa Agano la Kale waliona hukumu ikitokea wakati wa uhamisho wa Waisraeli kwenda Babuloni. Waandishi wa Agano Jipya wanatumia kifungu <em>Siku ya</em> <em>Bwana</em> kuelezea kurudi kwa Yesu kama hakimu wa dunia. Siku hiyo &quot;itakuja kama mwizi&quot; (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10\">2 Petro 3:10</a>; tazama pia <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:2-1Thess5:4\">1 Wathesalonike 5:2–4</a>). Kwa hiyo, watu wa Mungu lazima wawe tayari, la sivyo watapata mwisho sawa na wale waliopuuza maonyo ya manabii.</p><p><u>Sehemu za Kujifunza Zaidi</u></p><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:10-Isa2:22\">Isaya 2:10–22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:1-Isa4:6\">4:1–6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:4-Isa13:12\">13:4–12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:1-Ezek30:5\">Ezekieli 30:1–5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:13-Joel1:15\">Yoeli 1:13–15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:1-Joel2:11\">2:1–11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28-Joel2:32\">28–32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:9-Joel3:16\">3:9–16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18-Amos5:24\">Amosi 5:18–24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:15-Obad1:16\">Obadia 1:15–16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:2-Zeph1:18\">Sefania 1:2–18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:1-Mal4:5\">Malaki 4:1–5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:8\">1 Wakorintho 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:5\">5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:2\">1 Wathesalonike 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:2\">2 Wathesalonike 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:18\">2 Timotheo 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10\">2 Petro 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1-Rev20:15\">Ufunuo 20:1–15</a></p>",
